title.rendered: Surgimask Level 3 Tie Back – 160mmHg, Box of 50

content.rendered:
The Surgimask Level 3 surgical mask is suitable for the user who is at the highest risk of exposure to body and body fluids as well as risk of potential infection.

  • the practitioner and clinician during surgical procedures
  • front line workers
  • dental workers
  • allied health professional

A level 3 Surgical Mask is also suitable for the public to wear to reduce the risk of potential infection and high risk of fluid contact with those in close proximity.

The Strapit Surgimask is the highest quality Level 3 mask meeting all world standards including:
– Australia: AS 4381:2015
– Europe: EN14683
– USA: ASTM3

excerpt.rendered:
• Fluid resistance of 160mmHg/16.0kPa in accordance with ASTM F1862-98 & ASTM F1862-00a
  • BFE > 99% – bacterial filtration at 0.3 microns
  • PFE >95% – viral filtration at 0.1 microns
  • Mask Breathability (Delta P)- excellent breathability with a low delta  ensuring maximum comfort and coolness when in use.
  • Available in Loop and Tie Back- Tie bakc masks allow for a better fit to different shaped heads.
